description: CCCC MS 241 contains seventeenth-century transcriptions of six letters written by Richard Cox (c.1500-1581), Bishop of Ely. The first five are to Heinrich Bullinger (1504-1575), the sixth letter is to Wolfgang Weidner. The first four letters and the sixth date to the 1550s but the fifth letter, dated to 1559 in the MS, has been dated to sometime after 27 July 1571 based on its contents.
